\[ (x+18)(x-16) = 0 \]
This gives us two possible zero solutions: \( x = -18 \) and \( x = 16 \). Since we are looking for positive even integers, we discard \( x = -18 \). Thus, the two consecutive integers 16 and 18, and the greater integer is 18.
